RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH PRANCER showed speed leaving the break and contested the solid early pace with CEE'S THE IMAGE, was given a breather along the turn and pressed that rival to the quarter marker, re-engaged leaving the bend, came in a bit in upper stretch and brushed with CEE'S THE IMAGE, shook free from CEE'S THE IMAGE heading to mid-stretch, was kept to task into the final sixteenth and drove clear under hand urging in deep stretch. CEE'S THE IMAGE was asked to show early speed leaving the break, engaged with IRISH PRANCER and disputed solid fractions heading to the turn, took a narrow lead along the bend then dueled with IRISH PRANCER into upper stretch, brushed with that rival at the three-sixteenths marker, could not match strides with the winner into the final furlong and held safely for the place at the finish. CATTIN ALL AROUND took back to track the dueling pacesetters early on, tracked two wide through the turn, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, lacked a final response in deep stretch and held safely for the show. DESERT RUMBLE was a bit slow away from the gate, chased the solid pace from the rear into the turn, swung four wide into the drive, made up ground in the final stages but was unable to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Desert Rumble
ENTRY.COMMENT: off bit slow,chased 2wide,4wide into stretch,gained,no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Cattin All Around
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace 2wide,3wide into stretch,no final bid,held 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Cee's the Image
ENTRY.OWNER: Hill Laurie LeAnne and Hill Steven

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 98. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 18000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 13 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances Only).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOIC LUNA settled off of the early pace while outside of rivals and not far back, improved position along the backstretch run while in the clear and three deep, moved into contention along the far turn while three wide, mounted a four wide bid into upper stretch, overtook HARBOR ABBEY inside of the three-sixteenths marker, drew to a clear lead inside of the furlong pole and was ridden out in the final stages as much the best. BUSKER ALLIE was away a step slowly from the gate and was allowed to settle, saved ground while inching closer through the backstretch run, was coaxed along outside of rivals into the far turn and was roused three wide into the stretch, gained ground heading to the furlong marker, could not keep pace with STOIC LUNA in the final stages but stayed on to win the nod for the place on the wire. SHANGHAI MIST tracked the early pace from a ground saving position, was well placed through the backstretch run and saved ground into the far turn, waited for a few strides behind a tiring rival in upper stretch then tipped two wide for the drive and ran evenly to mid-stretch, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch and just missed for the place, while clear in the end for the show. HARBOR ABBEY stalked the decent early pace from a two wide path, moved up along the backstretch run, vied for the lead while between runners nearing the quarter marker, took a narrow lead in upper stretch, could not match strides with STOIC LUNA heading to the furlong pole and gave way in deep stretch. PROOF OF JAZZ assumed command leaving the start and dictated terms into the first turn, set decent fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure nearing the top of the stretch and was overtaken, chased to the furlong marker and tired in the final sixteenth.

ENTRY.NAME: Busker Allie
ENTRY.OWNER: Bellasis Tim Lafever Bennie D and Tschanz Cassandra
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow,settled inside,bid 3wide,needed more,ran on,nod 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Shanghai Mist
ENTRY.OWNER: Kelly Benjamin E and Taylor Faith

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 12500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE EYED JO took back to track the contentious early pace, maintained a three wide path into the turn and chased to the quarter marker, was coaxed along five wide into the stretch, commenced a wide rally and vied for the lead at the furlong pole, took a narrow lead into the final sixteenth, kept to task to deep stretch and held in a drive in the end to prevail. CALIGRAPHY was allowed to settle in the early running, raced two wide along the turn then was angled four wide into the stretch, loomed at the furlong pole, battled with BLUE EYED JO to the final sixteenth, was outfinished in deep stretch and bested the rest. THE RIVER MANGITA lacked early speed and saved ground into the turn, swung three wide for the drive and advanced heading to the furlong marker, split rivals approaching the final sixteenth, could not impact the top pair in deep stretch and held safely in the end for the show. AUTISM SHINE broke alertly and showed good early speed leaving the gate, contested the quick early pace while two wide between runners into the turn, continued to battle while between runners into the turn, took a narrow lead into upper stretch, was confronted by the top pair at the furlong marker, could not match strides into deep stretch and faded. RUNAWAY SALLY was sent to be forwardly placed in the early running, pressed the solid pace while three wide and outside of rivals into the turn, vied for the lead while three deep nearing the quarter marker, battled with AUTISM SHINE into the stretch but could not keep pace into the final stages and gave way. VALERIE was asked for early speed and contested the solid early pace while inside of rivals, disputed the pace from the rail along the turn, lost position into upper stretch and tired in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Valerie
ENTRY.COMMENT: asked for speed,contested pace inside,lost position 3/16,tired

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Eyed Jo
ENTRY.OWNER: Domeyko Taylor LP Moger Inc S Tsujimoto LLC Estrada Aldo and Pimentel Paul

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 94. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $32,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Cal Bred or Cal Sired Horses that have won the Open First Condition Allowance Race in Northern California must carry an Additional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOMMA MOCCA unhurried from the break, settled near the back of pack while never far behind, raced in the two path in hand, gained ground through the turn without much effort, responded when roused at the top of the stretch then launched a bold rally to prevail. DERRYGOOLIN off a beat slow, settled behind the early pace racing in the three path, launched a sustained bid from the three furlong marker, battled a game TOPANTICIPATION (GB) down the stretch, took a brief lead inside the sixteenth marker but could not hold off the winner in the final yards. TOPANTICIPATION (GB) broke in at the break and brushed with DRAW ME, was then hustled to the front and grabbed the rail position, shook off SHEZAGHOST at the six furlong marker, was responding to rating tactics by the rider down the backstretch, quickened into the far turn, still had some run when set down in the stretch and battled on gamely but was outfinished inside the sixteenths pole. SHEZAGHOST was pushed to get forward position into the first turn, backed off at the six furlong pole and was content to track from a couple of lengths behind, was prompted to go after the lead inside the three furlong pole,quickened a bit but was unable to keep up and struggled in the late stages. DRAW ME had to steady after the break when TOP ANTICIPATION came over then was unhurried through the early stages while keeping to the inside, made steady forward progress to move into contention with MOMMA MOCCA matching strides on the outside, had to wait for racing room on the far turn then failed to make an impact when a hole opened up at the top of the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Topanticipation (GB)
ENTRY.OWNER: Charles, Ronald L. and Gordon, Samuel
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, hustled, rated on clear lead, battled gamely to 1/16

ENTRY.NAME: Draw Me
ENTRY.OWNER: Eaton Terri Gibson Joe H Sahud Jacqueline and Sahud Mervyn
ENTRY.COMMENT: steadied break, unhurried inside, waited far turn, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Shezaghost
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed first turn, ceded lead, tracked, bid 3/8, needed more

ENTRY.NAME: Derrygoolin
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled behind pace, sustained bid 3/8, brief lead, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Momma Mocca
ENTRY.OWNER: Gutierrez Matthew Hanna Mark A Hanna Maria and Martin Ralph
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, settled, responded when roused 1/4, bold rally to win

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 5 5F Turf CR: 83. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SONOFAFINCH was forwardly placed in the early running, took back off of the contentious pace and stalked from the rail along the turn, was well placed while saving ground nearing the top of the stretch, took command leaving the bend, drew to a clear lead under moderate urging inside of the furlong pole, was kept to task into deep stretch and held safely in a drive at the finish. GEORGE HERMAN RUTH was asked to show speed leaving the break and was prominent in the early running, disputed the solid pace while outside of rivals into the turn, pressed two wide along the bend, was floated out by the drifting COBRE nearing the quarter marker, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, came in tight in upper stretch, navigated traffic through the furlong marker, found room in the final sixteenth, closed in deep stretch and was up in time to secure the place. COBRE was hustled leaving the break and disputed the solid early pace, assumed command into the turn and set a pressured pace along the bend, was hard to place and drifted out nearing the quarter marker, recovered and came two wide into the stretch, chased SONOFAFINCH to the furlong grounds, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and held for third at the finish. MR. FIGHTER was sent leaving the break and pressed the solid early pace while widest early on, raced close to the pace while four wide along the turn, was floated out nearing the top of the stretch, ran in pursuit of SONOFAFINCH to the furlong marker, could not match strides into deep stretch and was outkicked, while holding for a share of third at the finish. EDDIE CROSSWIRE took back off of the early pace and tracked two wide into the turn, gave chase while two to three wide and between runners nearing the top of the stretch, angled five wide for the drive, lacked a late rally in the final furlong and passed tiring rivals in deep stretch. BIG DIFFERENCE chased the solid early pace while between runners, raced in tight quarters and checked out of a tight spot in the first furlong, ran in pursuit while along the rail on the turn, saved ground into upper stretch and lacked a late response. JERSEY BABE raced close to the solid early pace, lost position into the turn and chased three wide to the quarter marker, swung widest into the stretch and came six wide for the drive, could not muster a late bid and gave way. ZHIVAGO chased the solid early pace from the inside, lost ground on the turn, angled four wide for the drive and ran evenly to mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final stages and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Difference
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased btwn early,checked 1/2,chased inside turn,no late response

ENTRY.NAME: Eddie Crosswire
ENTRY.OWNER: Bellasis Tim Smartt Donna and Tschanz Cassandra

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Babe
ENTRY.OWNER: Daehling Farms LLC and Tittle Morgan
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,chased 3wide turn,swung 6wide upper,gave way stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BROKEN FINGER was allowed to settle in the early stages while not far back, tracked the decent pace while outside of an inner rival through the backstretch run, was given his cue entering the far turn and mounted a four wide bid nearing the quarter marker, vied for the lead in upper stretch and took command inside of the three-sixteenths marker, responded to firm urging in the drive and drew clear in the final stages to prevail. GORDY'S BOY was unhurried in the early running, settled outside of rivals through the backstretch run, came three wide into the far turn and mounted a four wide rally into upper stretch, gained ground at the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outkicked, while besting the rest. LORD WIMBORNE (IRE) broke a step slowly leaving the start and was allowed to settle in the early running, saved all of the ground through the backstretch run and maintained that rail trip to the far turn, improved position and came within aim nearing the quarter marker, came in a bit tight approaching the top of the stretch, found room inside of the furlong marker, was not able to impact the top two in deep stretch but ran on and was up in time to secure the show. POUR ON THE COLE stalked the decent early pace from the inside, was well placed while saving ground approaching the second turn and was steered two wide to the quarter marker, waited for racing room approaching the top of the lane, shifted three wide for the drive, did not offer a final response in deep stretch and missed for the show. MASHHAD FLATS broke a step slowly and was hustled leaving the break, established the lead into the first turn and set decent fractions into the backstretch run, was prompted to the half-mile marker by MUCHO MACHISMO and contested the pace with that rival to the quarter pole, could not keep pace with BROKEN FINGER into upper stretch, chased the winner to the furlong grounds and weakened. MUCHO MACHISMO was sent leaving the break and was forwardly placed into the first turn, attended to the decent pace through the backstretch run and contested the pace while three wide into the far turn, took a narrow lead into upper stretch, was collared by BROKEN FINGER inside of the three-sixteenths pole, gave chase to mid-stretch and gave way in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Broken Finger
ENTRY.OWNER: Rivera Leobardo R and Sosa Manuela Franco

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Wimborne (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow,saved ground,in tight 3/16,not enough,ran on 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 80. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIAM'S SECRET was forwardly placed into the first turn and stalked the decent early pace from the inside, tracked the pacesetter through the backstretch run, was well placed while saving all of the ground to the quarter marker, made a steady gain into upper stretch and closed determinedly in the drive, confronted BLUEBERRY MUFFIN inside of the sixteenth-marker, dueled with that rival to the wire and gamely prevailed at the finish. BLUEBERRY MUFFIN lunged leaving the break but was away in good order and was sent to establish the early lead, drifted out along the first turn but recovered quickly and dictated terms into the backstretch run, was well rated through moderate fractions to the half-mile marker and showed the way to the quarter pole, came under pressure at mid-stretch, fended off challenges to the sixteenth-marker when confronted by LIAM'S SECRET, met that rival's bid to deep stretch, gamely battled to the wire and just missed for the win at the finish. KITTEN'S KID was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the pace while two then three wide into the backstretch run, tracked the pacesetter to the far turn, improved position while three wide nearing the quarter marker, responded to urging and continued that rally to mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final furlong, was outkicked and held for third at the finish. CHEERFUL CHARM a bit keen in the early running, settled outside of runners into the first turn and came five wide into the backstretch run, stalked the moderate pace to the far turn, improved position while four wide nearing the quarter marker, could not sustain that run into the stretch and lost ground at the furlong marker, lacked a final bid in deep stretch and missed for third. PRANCIN N THE PARK took back off of the early pace, was steered four wide into the backstretch run and stalked the pace while not far back approaching the half-mile marker, came in a bit tight entering the second turn and was shuffled back nearing the quarter marker, chased the leaders while two wide into the stretch and lacked a late rally. ST HELENA hopped leaving the break and was away slowly, trailed in the early stages, saved ground into the far turn and did not threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Cheerful Charm
ENTRY.OWNER: Harris Farms Inc and Der Manouel Michael

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ROSA RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 92. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUE SERA SIR RALPH was bumped at the start by VANISKY then hustled to contest the early pace, jumped a rough patch of grass near the finish line then got the rail and a share of the lead going into the first turn, cut the corner nicely and entered the backstretch with a clear advantage, held that lead to the far turn, responded when asked to quicken passing the three furlong pole, came into the stretch a little wide, opening up the rail for EL JOY to challenge from the inside then was also challenged by WINE AND WHISKEY to the outside, held a narrow advantage as the three foes separated themselves from the rest, dug in determinedly and dead-heated for the win in a game effort. WINE AND WHISKY got away well and was third from the rail as part of quartet contesting the pace into the first turn, took a three wide tracking position under some restraint for the backstretch run, continued racing wide through the far turn, responded to strong handling, came into the stretch three wide, battled the length of the stretch with QUE SERA SIR RALPH and hit the line together. EL JOY broke in and caused a minor chain reaction to the inside, raced mid-pack while saving ground to the inside, moved into striking position heading in the far turn, got a dream run up the rail for the stretch run, finished well and was gaining at the wire but fell just short. SUNNY SPOT encouraged some from the break but was unable to get inside, got fanned four wide through the clubhouse turn, continued wide on the far turn, came under a hard ride from the seven-sixteenths pole, ran on and made up some ground to finish in front of the second flank. BEROLIJEAN (FR) had no speed and lagged near the rear through the early stages, started to rally with three furlongs to go, swung about five wide into the stretch and was running on well but was never a threat to the top three. VANISKY got pinballed at the start, recovered to dispute the early pace going into the first turn, then was content to cede the lead through the early stages while tracking nicely just behind the leader, came under a ride approaching the quarter pole, was unable to match strides as the top three quickened away then finished up someone one-paced. SAFE COMBINATION was not asked for speed from the gate, was content to let the pace scenario play out in front while racing in the middle of the pack under some restraint, got boxed in from the five-eighths pole to the middle of the turn, had a clear path turning for home but was unable to quicken with the rest and chased the field to the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: Berolijean (FR)
ENTRY.COMMENT: lagged, rallied 3/8, 5wide bid stretch, ran on but no threat

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Que Sera Sir Ralph
ENTRY.COMMENT: set measured pace, battled between foes stretch, game effort

ENTRY.NAME: Vanisky
ENTRY.COMMENT: pinballed start, tracked behind leader, bid 1/4, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: El Joy
ENTRY.OWNER: Bellasis Tim Smartt Donna and Tschanz Cassandra
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, saved ground, rail run stretch, good finish, fell short

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Wine and Whisky
ENTRY.OWNER: Mean Girls Racing Stable (Tipton) and Fernandez Robert
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3wide trip, always close up, loomed far turn, good rally

ENTRY.NAME: Safe Combination
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved early, boxed in mid-race, unable quicken late

ENTRY.NAME: Sunny Spot
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide both turns, under drive 7/16, some finish, no match
